SIMPLE: excel
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Excel
<hw>Ex*cel"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Excelled</conjf><pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Excelling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>excellere</ets>,
<ets>excelsum</ets>; <ets>ex</ets> out + a root found in
<ets>culmen</ets> height, top; cf. F. <ets>exceller</ets>. See
<er>Culminate</er>, <er>Column</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To go
beyond or surpass in good qualities or laudable deeds; to outdo or
outgo, in a good sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Excelling</qex> others, these were great;⟦br⟧
Thou, greater still, must these <qex>excel</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I saw that wisdom <qex>excelleth</qex> folly, as far as light
<qex>excelleth</qex> darkness.</q> <rj><qau>Eccl. ii. 13.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To exceed or go beyond; to surpass.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She opened; but to shut⟦br⟧
<qex>Excelled</qex> her power; the gates wide open stood.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Excel</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Excel
<hw>Ex*cel"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To surpass others in good
qualities, laudable actions, or acquirements; to be distinguished by
superiority; <as>as, to <ex>excel</ex> in mathematics, or
classics</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Unstable as water, thou shalt not <qex>excel</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Gen. xlix. 4.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then peers grew proud in horsemanship t' <qex>excel</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Excellence</ent>⟦br⟧
